# migrated from tests/cases/wsc.chat (gen346, hermetic + isolated)
[mock hermetic]
!set PARROT0_BASE=
!set PARROT0_SESSION=
!set PARROT0_WORLD_FACTS=0
!set PARROT0_LANG=en
!reset

[test wsc]
# gen31: coreference decision — "does <a> refer to <b>?", the yes/no judgement
# the first SuperGLUE WSC question asks. Built on gen22's discourse model (a
# pronoun resolves to the most recent concrete entity). We judge against that
# salience state; full WSC syntactic binding is out of scope (Decision
# D-2026-06-15d). Held-out entities.
#
# With no antecedent yet, a pronoun resolves to nothing -> admit, don't guess.
> does he refer to dana?
< I don't know who he refers to.
# A concrete mention sets the discourse entity.
> dana is a pilot
< Learned: pilot(dana).
# Now the pronoun co-refers with dana, and not with a different name.
> does she refer to dana?
< Yes.
> does her refer to mara?
< No.
# A newer mention moves salience; the pronoun follows it.
> mara is a teacher
< Learned: teacher(mara).
> does she refer to mara?
< Yes.
> does she refer to dana?
< No.
# Two concrete mentions co-refer iff they are the same entity.
> does dana refer to dana?
< Yes.
> does dana refer to mara?
< No.
